The usually boring area of road planning has suddenly sparked intense debate with colourful alliances.
Libertarians have allied themselves with environmental groups and argue that the government should be able to use the small boxes to record the kilometres travelled – and possibly where they have been driven – and then use the information to calculate tax moes.
Tea Party is appalled.
The American Civil Rights Association (ACLU) is also deeply concerned and expresses a number of privacy concerns.
But, while Congress cannot agree on action, several states are not waiting any longer.
