Thousands of drivers have already tested tachographs, some of which are equipped with GPS surveillance.
This really is a must for our country.
“ It ’ s not something we ’ ll possibly use, ” said Hasan Ikhrata, Managing of the Southern California Assn. of Governments, who plans to record the mileage of all Californian drivers from 2025 onwards.
How we pay these taxes will change.
The technology is there.
The initiative comes at a time when the Highway Trust Fund, financed by the taxes paid by the Americans at the fuel pump, is bankrupt.
But America no not has as much fuel as it used to do.
Cars consume less petrol.
The government tax of 18.4 cents per gallon (less than 4 euro cents per litre) has not increased for 20 years.
Politicians do not dare to raise the tax by one cent at high prices.
