The relationship in question is not simply that of a drug trafficker, but that of a drug trafficker who supplies his lawyer with drugs.
Some of his communications were undoubtedly legitimate, because he was the advocate of these people.
But this went far beyond the bounds of a normal relationship between lawyer and client.
He counteracted police investigations as far as possible so that they could carry out their criminal activities.
Ditta brought his profession into disrepute.
He was too close to certain clients, in particular Scarborough, and he allowed his independence to be compromised.
