“ We are very hopeful that this type of vaccination strategy can help millions of smokers who have tried to stop trying out all the methods available on the market, but have seen that their nicotine addiction is stronger than these approaches, ” Cornell said.
The new vaccine contains a harmless virus that has been modified to contain the genetic information needed for the production of nicotine antibodies.
The virus selectively infects the liver cells, which then produce a constant stream of antibodies.
The antibodies hunt down the nicotine molecules in the blood and neutralize them before they reach the brain, so a smoker does not experience a nicotine high.
In experiments, vaccinated mice who were given nicotine maintained their normal level of activity.
By contrast, mice without vaccination would have taken “ time out, ” researchers declared, a sign that nicotine had reached their brain.
The experiments are described in the journal Science Translational Medicine.
Previous tobacco vaccines failed because of antibodies.
Vaccinations had to be given so often in order to maintain the antibody level that they were expensive and impractical.
But the cost of the new vaccine is probably much lower, because it turns liver cells into antibody factories.
As Professor Crystal said, a future vaccine for people, if safe, could be given to children before they were tempted to try a cigarette, thus preventing nicotine addiction.
But it is more likely that smokers would use it to stop.
“ They then know that when they start smoking again, they no longer feel any pleasure because of the nicotine vaccine, which helps them abandon their habit, ” he explains.
